reviewText:
This is a well-intentioned "home movie" that covers some sighting reports in Oregon.  Some of it is filmed in the couple's bedroom.  Very disappointing; but I've seen worse.
Not one that I'll be watching again.

I just finished watching this AWESOME to GREAT new bigfoot-sasquatch documentary  a lot wildlife scenes etc  POSSIBLE sasquatch evidence other TRUST ME ITS A MUST A++++++ thanks bill green ct sasquatch researcher Bristol,ct  :) :) :)
Very average film.  Nothing new or dynamic.
Not worth the $1.99 I paid to sit through it. They should pay you to watch this low budget guy in his house with camcorder production.
This movie was entertaining if nothing else. It was very enjoyable for me and I would recommend it if you have some time to kill.

Don't expect a slick bunch of editing, it is a simple documentation. The video of the 'baby big foot' partial leg with the knee and foot, was interesting. Looked real to me, that's why I gave it 3 stars.
To short, ran out of people to interview,The author should had stay lost in the forest with big foot. But he tried.
boring , lack of decent evidence or sciencetist involved
